1- git init
2- creating/modifying/etc
3- git add <file>/<.>
   git checkout -- <file> # Undo the changes
4- git commit 
	or 
   git commit -m "<message>"
git commit will open a text editor (I think it is nano)

5- Create a new repository on Github.com
6- git remote add origin <link>
7- git push -u origin master #Envia os commits de uma Branch pro repositório remoto se não detectar conflitos
	-> First time: git push -u origin master
	   Then: git push <remote> <branch>
	-> After that you only need to git push
8- Add a README.md (md is markdown)

** git config --global core.editor #To change the editor
